  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Neha, I'm Miss Maya. Honestly, the way rain patters on a rooftop at night makes me feel cozy — like the whole world is sighing with me. How was your day?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey Maya! Not too bad, just a bit lonely today. Was stuck in a meeting all afternoon — you know how that goes. After work, I grabbed a coffee and people-watched at this cute little café. Rain at night does have that cozy vibe, but I missed it today. By the way, do you listen to music when it rains?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds like a slow afternoon. Coffee and people-watching fix loneliness a little. I get that — music and rain go hand in hand. What kind of music do you like when it rains?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Indie folk, mostly. There’s something about the gentle strumming and soft vocals that matches the mood of a rainy day. I also throw on some lo-fi sometimes — you know, the kind with light beats and chill samples. Oh, and I’ve been into this Tamil indie band lately, *Vaigai Porai* — their songs feel like they were made for rainy afternoons. Have you heard of them?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I like that combo — gentle music and soft rain. Tamil indie is such a fresh sound. I haven’t heard of them yet, but I’ll look them up. What’s your favourite song of theirs?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Kaalai Kettupen\" is my go-to — it’s so mellow and poetic. The way they blend traditional Tamil lyrics with modern indie vibes? Perfection. You should check it out, it feels like a hug on a rainy day. Anyway, I should probably get back to work. Talk to you later, Maya?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Kaalai Kettupen\" sounds like the kind of song that wraps around you. I will — when it rains again. Work calls? Of course, take your time — I’m here whenever you want to practice."
    }
  ],
